title: Grateful Dead Live at Charlotte Coliseum on 1984-10-05
description:
Set 1

Bertha  ->
The Promised Land  
West L.A. Fadeaway  
Little Red Rooster  
Dupree's Diamond Blues  
My Brother Esau  
Brown Eyed Women  
Feel Like A Stranger  
Might As Well  

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower  ->
I Know You Rider  
Estimated Prophet  ->
Eyes Of The World  ->
Drums  ->
Space  ->
The Other One  ->
Black Peter  ->
Sugar Magnolia   ->
Johnny B. Goode  

Encore
It's All Over Now, Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: sloppy show esp s2 1st set is pretty good, but honestly s2 is quite sloppy, gasping for air. Yes, a good deal of 84 has that 'junky' kind of delivery and is still great, but this one just isn't as good as many others in the period.
great effort, great story, great recording thank you!   this one sounds great.

Agreeeeeeeeeeee Love your story of things went down.Not sure why but I remember the energy off the charts at this show. I coulod care less when others say Junkie Jerry stuff.He is what he is back then our favortie in the band giving it his all day in and day out pushing it further and further. Loved it then love it now 30 years later.
 I have found a new appreciation for you guys that did the work so we can relive the momeries of our life. Where else can one go to relive listen and love this band. Maybe heaven when the time comes.
- Started off pretty good, but went shaky after not too long. Weird, horrible noises in Estimated. I can't stand the way they used to rush Eyes in this era. Not my thing.

Best of Times Great recording and nice write up. 1984 was my sweet spot saw them 27 times that year but missed the southern start to this rocking fall. Thanks for your sharing the sounds and your memories. Onwards to the 30th anniversary of Augusta!!
84 Dead Rocks! This show is solid! and the 2nd set is great, China Rider/estimated Black peter, All top notch. 1st set is ALL great!
